WEBVTT

00:01.200 --> 00:03.520
PREVIOUSLY

00:03.840 --> 00:05.360
The police are looking for you.

00:05.560 --> 00:08.200
I want to go where my accident happened,
then I'll go back.

00:08.400 --> 00:11.760
You took an overdose and
only just pulled through.

00:12.520 --> 00:16.400
I would like some information regarding
my treatment by Dr Mommaerts.

00:18.200 --> 00:20.160
Oh, Mie.
- Not all of them.

00:20.360 --> 00:21.120
Here.

00:21.320 --> 00:22.680
MEDICAL RECORDS
ANNEMIE D'HAEZE

00:22.880 --> 00:24.600
Vronsky.

00:24.800 --> 00:26.120
Goddammit.

00:26.400 --> 00:29.040
You're a dirty rat.
Vronsky the rat.

00:29.240 --> 00:32.680
Only one lunatic in here rips pages
out of books and that's you.

00:37.120 --> 00:38.040
Bob.

00:48.080 --> 00:51.400
I met Benoit at a premiere,
he was there with Veronique.

00:51.600 --> 00:54.280
He finished with her first
before he started seeing me.

00:54.480 --> 00:56.040
I'll tell you what happened.

00:56.240 --> 01:00.600
While my daughter suffered from depression
because she was at her wit's end with Romy

01:00.800 --> 01:05.160
and sir here had to go and fuck his ex.
- Yes, that happened.

01:05.360 --> 01:07.720
I had nothing more to do with Veronique
from then on.

01:07.920 --> 01:09.640
CALL ME XXX V.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.600
I want to leave. With you.
- OK.

01:12.800 --> 01:14.640
Back here at 4 o'clock.

01:14.840 --> 01:16.560
Benoit, I'm leaving you.

01:16.760 --> 01:20.080
You have to remember
what happened to that Thomas Spectre.

01:20.280 --> 01:23.000
He's the drunk
who drove into your car, Mie.

02:37.600 --> 02:41.960
We cannot tear out
a single page of our life,

02:42.160 --> 02:45.200
but we can throw the whole book
in the fire.

02:47.240 --> 02:48.920
George Sand.

03:04.240 --> 03:07.560
TODAY
13 DECEMBER

03:22.560 --> 03:23.920
Mie?

03:30.280 --> 03:32.920
How are you doing?
- OK.

03:33.120 --> 03:36.280
Mie, Jan Peeters died in hospital
this morning.

03:36.720 --> 03:37.760
Who's he?

03:38.440 --> 03:42.080
Vronsky.
- The patient with the split personality.

03:45.160 --> 03:48.360
But you only knew him as Vronsky.

03:52.840 --> 03:54.440
Where did you get that?

03:57.040 --> 03:58.920
He gave it to me.

04:00.640 --> 04:04.680
And... how did he get hold of
that model airplane and the methanol?

04:08.040 --> 04:09.480
I don't know.

04:09.680 --> 04:12.920
Mr Peeters didn't have any visitors.
Nor did Vronsky.

04:14.520 --> 04:18.800
You had a good relationship with him, eh?
- Inspector Wolkers visited him.

04:19.720 --> 04:22.800
Would he give an inflammable toy
to a pyromaniac?

04:23.000 --> 04:25.440
He must have had matches too.

04:26.720 --> 04:29.800
Did he get those
from the inspector as well?

04:32.800 --> 04:34.440
I don't know.

04:37.120 --> 04:40.840
Then we'll have to ask
the inspector himself, won't we?

04:45.360 --> 04:48.480
I don't retire till tomorrow.
- No, Jacques, it stops here.

04:48.680 --> 04:51.280
I have the right to finish my case,
don't I? Dammit.

04:51.480 --> 04:53.480
You're stuck, Jacques.

04:53.680 --> 04:55.720
And not just in your case.

04:57.400 --> 04:59.640
We took the husband's complaint seriously.

04:59.840 --> 05:02.600
I've also taken the time
to look at your case.

05:02.800 --> 05:05.480
It's not ethical, goddammit.

05:11.280 --> 05:13.960
I suppose he got his good looks
from his mum?

05:14.160 --> 05:19.240
You know the rules. Covering up personal
involvement means immediate suspension.

05:20.800 --> 05:25.320
And I'd prefer it if we can ensure
your career doesn't end with a blemish.

05:26.080 --> 05:29.240
Right, come on. E1 to H1.

05:38.280 --> 05:39.480
24 more hours.

05:39.800 --> 05:43.200
No, no, no.
We are going to do it by the book.

05:43.400 --> 05:46.120
You do remember
how you ended up on that chair, eh?

05:46.320 --> 05:50.520
And I'm very grateful to you.
I'm just trying to protect you.

05:50.720 --> 05:52.680
You're not going to deter me.

05:57.000 --> 05:58.680
A2 to A1.

06:05.560 --> 06:06.800
Stalemate.

06:14.280 --> 06:16.320
Here, your leaving gift.

06:16.520 --> 06:18.840
From your own party that you missed.

06:22.120 --> 06:23.760
It may come in handy.

06:24.920 --> 06:26.640
24 hours.

06:27.320 --> 06:29.240
Use them well.

06:37.680 --> 06:42.320
Inspector? Inspector, a quick word
about Jan Peeters' death?

06:42.520 --> 06:43.880
A very unfortunate affair.

06:44.080 --> 06:47.720
He wasn't the first to take his own life
here but the way he did it...

06:47.920 --> 06:52.240
What mainly worries us is how he got hold
of that model airplane and the matches.

06:52.440 --> 06:54.720
Model airplane?
What has that got to do with it?

06:54.920 --> 06:58.400
It used methanol. It's highly inflammable.
- I know what methanol is.

07:00.640 --> 07:04.200
Shouldn't you be more worried about
Annemie D'Haeze being able to escape?

07:04.440 --> 07:06.560
And now you'll have to excuse me.

07:06.760 --> 07:10.040
I have a disappearance to solve
and other things to worry about

07:10.240 --> 07:13.600
than some sad lunatic
who barbecued himself.

07:17.160 --> 07:19.920
Well? Why did we run away?

07:25.520 --> 07:28.200
I've heard the terrible news
about your friend.

07:28.880 --> 07:32.000
Come on, Mie. Why did we run away?

07:32.640 --> 07:34.680
I had to see
where your son and my daughter...

07:34.880 --> 07:37.440
We've had that conversation already, Mie.

07:37.800 --> 07:41.200
And my relationship with my son
has nothing to do with this.

07:41.400 --> 07:44.520
You're looking for a scapegoat.
- And you have a motive.

07:45.680 --> 07:48.720
I'm not the only one.
- That's true.

07:49.480 --> 07:54.000
But your husband was at work.
His colleagues have confirmed that again.

07:54.680 --> 07:57.120
And he wasn't the last person
seen with Thomas, Mie.

08:35.960 --> 08:38.080
That's Bob.
- Bob?

08:40.080 --> 08:41.240
Yes.

08:43.400 --> 08:45.120
I'm Gust.

08:46.880 --> 08:49.440
Why do you say Bob?
- The gamekeeper.

08:49.640 --> 08:53.040
Yes, the gamekeeper.
He found you in the woods.

08:53.920 --> 08:56.040
Sit down, Gust. Sit down.

09:03.120 --> 09:05.280
Tell me what you saw.

09:06.240 --> 09:12.440
First I saw the young lady go into
the woods and a bit later Mr Spectre.

09:12.640 --> 09:14.920
Together? You saw them together?

09:15.240 --> 09:18.760
Yes. Earlier in the day.
In that little chalet.

09:20.760 --> 09:22.880
I think they often met up there.

09:23.080 --> 09:27.080
What happened there?
What did they do?

09:31.840 --> 09:33.080
They had sex there?

09:36.120 --> 09:40.920
Then what? What happened afterwards?
Did they leave together?

09:41.320 --> 09:46.440
No. I didn't see the man again that day.

09:47.320 --> 09:50.480
But I did see the young lady.
Later in the woods.

09:51.320 --> 09:55.320
Completely exhausted. Covered in blood.
In a right state.

09:56.600 --> 09:58.120
I knew where she lived.

09:59.360 --> 10:03.320
Of course you know where I live.
You've been watching me for months.

10:05.840 --> 10:08.200
Carry on, Gust.

10:08.400 --> 10:12.200
I tried to calm her down
and took her home.

10:12.400 --> 10:16.240
That's true. Your mother confirmed that.
She was at your house.

10:17.960 --> 10:22.600
And then a few days later
I saw that missing person notice.

10:22.800 --> 10:27.800
So I called the police immediately.
- This isn't Gust.

10:28.760 --> 10:33.160
He's lying. This is Bob. His name is Bob
and he's trying to trick me.

10:33.760 --> 10:38.280
He is. Can't you see through him?
Can't you see through his little game?

10:38.480 --> 10:41.800
Of course he came forward as a witness.
I told you, he knows all about me.

10:42.000 --> 10:45.560
He hangs around my house. He knows
everything, he knows about my amnesia.

10:45.760 --> 10:49.280
He knows about Romy. He knows about
my husband and Tom, where we meet.

10:49.480 --> 10:53.840
He knows everything. He killed Tom.
And you're trying to blame it on me.

10:54.040 --> 10:56.680
Miss.
- Look at his jacket. There's blood on it.

10:56.880 --> 10:59.560
Calm down. Calm down.
- No. Don't.

10:59.760 --> 11:01.000
Calm down.

11:03.680 --> 11:05.400
Gust, Gust.
Tell me, Mie.

11:05.600 --> 11:09.080
He's done something terrible to Tom...
You have to... Let go of me.

11:09.280 --> 11:13.120
He's... He's got a cabin in the woods.
Let go of me. You have to check it.

11:13.320 --> 11:15.840
He did it. He killed Tom.

11:16.520 --> 11:19.920
Calm down, calm down.
- Let go of me. No, don't touch me.

12:10.760 --> 12:14.120
TODAY
14 DECEMBER

12:26.200 --> 12:27.320
Hello, Mie.

12:31.800 --> 12:34.240
Hi.
- I need something to write with.

12:34.440 --> 12:36.840
What?
- Something to write with.

12:37.560 --> 12:40.760
Hurry up... Hurry up...

12:42.320 --> 12:43.760
Here you are.

12:49.160 --> 12:51.400
Did they put you in here
because you ran away?

13:00.120 --> 13:02.320
Wolkers was right.

13:04.280 --> 13:07.520
That Bob isn't the gamekeeper.

13:08.280 --> 13:11.720
The Bob in my dream isn't a person.

13:13.840 --> 13:16.720
I have to take Mrs D'Haeze
back to her room.

13:18.520 --> 13:19.320
Right.

13:24.400 --> 13:27.320
But we've searched these woods already,
haven't we?

13:30.160 --> 13:32.960
Uh, chief. We've already done this once.

13:33.760 --> 13:38.760
Fed up with your job, Meulemans? You can
go and issue parking tickets, if you want.

13:53.040 --> 13:57.720
May I stay a while longer? I'm her doctor.
- I want her to stay.

14:00.320 --> 14:02.080
Mie, what is this?

14:03.680 --> 14:06.360
There was someone else.
- Where?

14:06.560 --> 14:11.440
At my accident. There was someone
with a key ring like that.

14:11.640 --> 14:15.920
A paramedic or a fireman.
- No, no, no. Before that.

14:17.560 --> 14:20.160
Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm sure. I saw it.

14:20.360 --> 14:23.080
In my dream.
- A dream?

14:23.280 --> 14:28.680
No, it was... It was more than a dream.
I remember it.

14:29.000 --> 14:32.840
Yes, but... how we remember things
is almost never how it really happened,

14:33.040 --> 14:35.280
certainly not in the case of
people with amnesia.

14:36.440 --> 14:39.040
The doctors did warn you
about confabulations.

14:39.240 --> 14:44.040
People who lose their memory often
try to fill the gaps with a fantasy.

14:44.240 --> 14:47.520
Romy was a fantasy for a long time.
- No, it's more than a fantasy.

14:47.720 --> 14:51.920
I'm telling you, they are trying to
trick me. They want to keep me here.

14:52.120 --> 14:55.440
Mie, your paranoia is destroying
everyone around you.

14:55.640 --> 14:57.480
Your mother, Benoit, yourself.

15:00.760 --> 15:03.880
You have to help me.
I have to get out of here.

15:04.080 --> 15:07.640
I want to help you, I really do, but you
are focussing too much on the accident,

15:07.840 --> 15:12.440
you should concentrate on Thomas Spectre.
- But the two are connected.

15:20.560 --> 15:21.920
Jonas.

15:30.480 --> 15:31.720
Fuck.

15:33.600 --> 15:38.040
Mie, come on... You slept with Thomas,
the man who killed your child.

15:38.240 --> 15:40.600
What did you do
after you found that out?

15:41.280 --> 15:43.120
I don't know.

15:43.440 --> 15:46.640
Try to go back to those feelings.
It will help you remember.

15:48.880 --> 15:52.520
Mie, you had sex with the man
who killed your daughter.

15:52.720 --> 15:53.840
But I didn't know.

15:55.000 --> 15:57.040
You have to remember.

15:57.400 --> 16:00.840
Now is the time. There is no other way.
You have to do it.

16:04.320 --> 16:06.160
Thomas Spectre is the drunk...

16:06.360 --> 16:07.640
DAY OF THE DISAPPEARANCE

16:07.840 --> 16:09.920
... who drove into your car, Mie.

16:11.880 --> 16:14.640
Go and fuck our daughter's killer.

16:56.600 --> 17:00.320
HALF, NO MORE
SLEEP WELL XXX

17:26.960 --> 17:28.440
You're here.

17:30.160 --> 17:33.600
Put that photo away.
I know who you are.

17:40.120 --> 17:42.280
I haven't been able
to stop thinking about you.

17:43.640 --> 17:45.280
Me too.

17:50.960 --> 17:52.760
You haven't got much with you.

17:53.280 --> 17:55.240
I don't need much.

18:14.480 --> 18:15.880
To us?

18:18.080 --> 18:20.280
I'm going to make you happy, Mie.

18:49.880 --> 18:52.120
Are you going to make me happy?

18:53.320 --> 18:55.320
Mie.
- Don't say my name.

19:06.640 --> 19:09.680
What else are you going to tell me? Eh?

19:12.360 --> 19:17.240
That it wasn't on purpose?
That you didn't kill my child on purpose?

19:25.960 --> 19:28.360
Why did you come looking for me?

19:29.920 --> 19:31.400
Why?

19:32.200 --> 19:34.600
Why did you start following me?

19:36.040 --> 19:38.400
You just screwed me over, you did.

19:49.800 --> 19:51.720
You took everything away from me.

19:52.520 --> 19:54.520
I couldn't help it.

19:57.440 --> 20:01.640
You suddenly turned up at the...
recycling centre.

20:04.440 --> 20:06.320
You didn't recognise me.

20:09.720 --> 20:12.040
I wanted to know if you were OK.

20:15.520 --> 20:17.720
You should've left me alone.

20:18.640 --> 20:19.960
I wanted...

20:20.800 --> 20:22.600
I was given a second chance...

20:23.800 --> 20:25.760
to make amends.

20:33.920 --> 20:36.440
For the first time since the accident

20:37.200 --> 20:38.920
I felt a sort of...

20:39.960 --> 20:41.320
peace...

20:42.720 --> 20:44.200
when you looked at me.

20:45.400 --> 20:48.440
I tried to fight it but...

20:50.800 --> 20:54.000
You felt it too.
- No. Don't say that.

20:54.200 --> 20:55.400
It was real.

21:01.120 --> 21:02.880
I'm sorry, Mie.

21:06.520 --> 21:09.680
I'm sorry that I killed your child.

21:16.080 --> 21:18.960
I love you, Mie.
- Don't say that.

21:25.200 --> 21:26.440
Mie.

21:33.320 --> 21:34.440
Mie.

21:35.200 --> 21:36.280
Mie.

22:43.080 --> 22:45.280
TODAY
14 DECEMBER

22:45.480 --> 22:48.960
How long have I been here?
- About ten days.

22:49.960 --> 22:55.480
Then he's been there more than a week.
- Mie? Mie, take it easy. No, sit down.

22:55.680 --> 22:57.640
What's the matter?

23:02.560 --> 23:04.240
I forgot about him.

23:04.720 --> 23:08.640
I shut him in the cellar of the cabin
in the woods and he's still there.

23:10.600 --> 23:15.000
OK.
You'll have to call Inspector Wolkers.

23:15.680 --> 23:17.920
I can't do that.
I have a duty of confidentiality.

23:18.120 --> 23:22.920
The sooner you tell him, the more chance
there is of Thomas being found alive.

23:49.240 --> 23:51.440
And?
- Just animal remains.

23:51.640 --> 23:53.360
No human remains.

23:53.560 --> 23:55.400
Are you sure?
- Yes.

23:57.320 --> 23:58.720
Wolkers?

23:59.840 --> 24:01.320
Mrs D'Haeze?

24:06.360 --> 24:07.400
Cabin in the woods, now!

24:20.800 --> 24:23.000
Do you still remember your dream?

24:24.320 --> 24:27.040
About forgetting about your rabbit
in the cellar?

24:29.600 --> 24:31.520
Dreams are strange things.

24:32.520 --> 24:36.120
They're the only place
where we can talk to our subconscious.

24:38.640 --> 24:40.400
What have I done?

24:48.160 --> 24:49.880
Oh, the letters.

24:50.720 --> 24:51.680
Letters?

24:51.880 --> 24:54.840
I probably wrote
all these letters myself too.

24:57.200 --> 24:58.920
I'M SORRY

24:59.120 --> 25:02.120
You wanted to tell yourself what you did.

25:04.880 --> 25:07.440
Beware the wolf in sheep's clothing.

25:07.640 --> 25:10.880
Their lies are so powerful
that eyes become blind.

25:11.080 --> 25:12.440
You were right.

25:14.880 --> 25:16.760
There wasn't anyone else.

25:19.720 --> 25:21.800
It's all in my head.

25:25.800 --> 25:27.400
Move that sofa.

25:33.640 --> 25:35.000
Goddammit.

25:45.560 --> 25:47.520
Christ, what a stench!

25:48.280 --> 25:51.000
Mie, is it OK
if I take my phone back?

26:03.480 --> 26:04.800
Thank you.

26:05.600 --> 26:08.240
We can carry on seeing each other,
if you want.

26:10.760 --> 26:15.400
Excuse me, the police have asked us
to put Mie in isolation so...

26:15.600 --> 26:20.200
I'm going to take this too.
I'll keep it for you, Mie.

26:20.640 --> 26:23.640
You don't need to worry
and you can stay in your room,

26:23.840 --> 26:27.240
but no visitors for now.
Until there is more news.

26:27.440 --> 26:28.840
I understand.

26:33.200 --> 26:35.000
It'll all be fine.

27:31.240 --> 27:34.000
<i>You have one new message.</i>

27:34.200 --> 27:38.400
<i>Hello, Mrs D'Haeze, St Anthony's here.
About your hospital treatment,</i>

27:38.600 --> 27:42.120
<i>you were treated during that period
by psychiatrist Dr Mommaerts.</i>

27:42.320 --> 27:45.840
<i>You were his last patient.
The man has since retired.</i>

27:46.040 --> 27:48.280
I hope that...
- Message deleted.

27:48.480 --> 27:51.120
<i>You have listened to all new messages.</i>

28:11.640 --> 28:17.720
